  "model_paragraph": "The line graph illustrates how people aged 16 to 25 in the UK obtained their news from 1980 to the present day, measured in millions. Overall, television was the dominant source for most of the period, while the internet rose from almost nothing to become the leading source by the end. In 1980, hardly any young people used the internet, but the figure shot up after 2000, overtaking newspapers around 2010 to reach six million. Television topped the table throughout most of this period, peaking at nine million before a slow decline to six million today. Newspapers, by contrast, saw a steady fall, slumping from seven million to just two million over the years.",
